00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:21,400
Take a guess how many
people are on my payroll.
Oskar.

454
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:27,200
My father, at the height
of his success, had 50.
I've got 350.

455
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:31,500
350 workers on the factory floor,
with one purpose.

456
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,800
To make pots and pans?

457
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:37,900
To make money.
For me.

458
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:40,300
[Sighs]

459
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:46,800
Does anyone ask about me?

460
00:36:48,300 --> 00:36:51,500
Back home?
Everybody.

461
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:54,500
All the time.

462
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:57,900
Hmm.

463
00:36:57,900 --> 00:37:03,500
They won't soon forget
the name Schindler here,
I can tell you that.

464
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:08,200
''Oskar Schindler,''
they'll say.

465
00:37:08,300 --> 00:37:11,700
''Everybody remembers him.

466
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:16,200
''He did something
extraordinary.

467
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:21,400
''He did something
no one else did.

468
00:37:21,500 --> 00:37:24,800
''He came here with nothing--

469
00:37:24,900 --> 00:37:27,800
''a suitcase--

470
00:37:27,900 --> 00:37:33,500
''and built a bankrupt
company into a major manufactory.

471
00:37:33,500 --> 00:37:37,100
''And left with
a steamer trunk--

472
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:41,800
''Two steamer trunks
full of money,

473
00:37:41,900 --> 00:37:46,200
all the riches of the world.''

474
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:48,200
Hmm.

475
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:51,500
It's comforting to see
that nothing's changed.

476
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:55,200
You're wrong, Emilie.
[Kissing Sound]

477
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:57,700
There's no way I could have
known this before,

478
00:37:57,700 --> 00:38:01,200
but there was always
something missing.

479
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:05,300
In every business I tried,
I can see now, it wasn't me
that failed.

480
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:08,200
Something was missing.

481
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:11,800
Even if I'd known what it
was, there's nothing I could
have done about it...

482
00:38:11,900 --> 00:38:16,500
because you can't
create this thing.

483
00:38:16,600 --> 00:38:21,900
And it makes all
the difference in the world
between success and failure.

484
00:38:21,900 --> 00:38:24,500
Luck?

485
00:38:26,900 --> 00:38:29,800
War.

486
00:38:53,300 --> 00:38:57,000
Should I stay?

487
00:38:57,100 --> 00:39:01,900
It's a beautiful city.

488
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:06,900
I asked you
if I should stay.

489
00:39:06,900 --> 00:39:10,000
It's up to you.

490
00:39:13,900 --> 00:39:18,500
Promise me, Oskar,
no doorman or maitre d'
will ever presume...

491
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:24,000
I'm anyone other than Mrs. Schindler,
and I'll stay.

492
00:39:26,200 --> 00:39:28,500
Good-bye, darling.

493
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:33,800
[Indistinct German]

494
00:39:45,100 --> 00:39:49,300
I could try to read this
or I could eat my lunch while it's still hot.

495
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:51,400
We're doing well?

496
00:39:51,500 --> 00:39:52,700
- Yes.
- Better this month than last?

497
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:55,100
- Yes.
- Any reason to think next month
will be worse?

498
00:39:55,100 --> 00:39:58,400
The war could end.

499
00:40:08,300 --> 00:40:10,900
- What?
- There is a machinist outside...

500
00:40:10,900 --> 00:40:14,000
who'd like to thank you
personally for giving him a job.

501
00:40:14,100 --> 00:40:18,800
Every day he comes. He's very grateful.
It'll just take a minute.

502
00:40:25,100 --> 00:40:27,500
Mr. Lowenstein?

503
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:37,600
I want to thank you, sir,

504
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,400
for giving me
the opportunity to work.

505
00:40:40,500 --> 00:40:43,400
You're welcome.
I'm sure you're doing a great job.

506
00:40:43,500 --> 00:40:47,800
The SS beat me up.
They would have killed me,

507
00:40:47,900 --> 00:40:52,600
but I am essential to the war effort,
thanks to you.

508
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:54,600
That's great.

509
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:57,300
I work hard for you.

510
00:40:57,300 --> 00:41:01,400
- I'm sure you do.
- I'll continue to work hard for you.

511
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:03,400
That's great.
Thanks.

512
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:06,000
- God bless you, sir.
- All right.

513
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,800
You are a good man.

514
00:41:11,200 --> 00:41:14,300
- He saved my life.
- Yes, he did.

515
00:41:14,300 --> 00:41:17,200
- God bless him.
- Yeah. Come on.

516
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:22,100
God bless you.

517
00:41:34,100 --> 00:41:37,000
[Stern]
I'm sorry, Herr Direktor,
but you're running very late.

518
00:41:37,100 --> 00:41:40,400
This is for the
Obersturmbannfuehrer, sir.

519
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:43,400
And this is for his niece,
Greta. It's her birthday.

520
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:46,200
Greta as in Garbo.
By the way, don't ever
do that to me again.

521
00:41:46,300 --> 00:41:48,900
Go. Go, go, drive!
Don't bow.

522
00:41:48,900 --> 00:41:52,900
- Did you happen to notice that
that man had one arm?
- What? Did he?

523
00:41:56,600 --> 00:41:59,200
- What's his use?
- Very useful.

524
00:42:01,900 --> 00:42:05,600
[Shouts]
- How?
- Very useful! Success!

525
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:18,200
##Achrar kach loe nedah ##

526
00:42:33,500 --> 00:42:36,700
[Officer]
Besen und Schaufeln
werden ausgeladen...

527
00:42:36,700 --> 00:42:39,400
jeder nimmt sich eine und dann
wird die Strasse gereinigt.

528
00:42:39,500 --> 00:42:41,700
We'll be late for work.

529
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:44,000
[Horn Honking]

530
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:57,100
[Rolf Czurda]
You shouldn't think of them
as yours, Oskar.

531
00:42:57,100 --> 00:42:59,100
You need to understand that
some of the officers here...

532
00:42:59,100 --> 00:43:01,900
don't give a damn
about production.

533
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:06,100
To them, it's a matter of,
um, national priority...

534
00:43:06,100 --> 00:43:08,500
that Jews
be made to shovel snow.

535
00:43:08,500 --> 00:43:11,100
It's got nothing to do
with reality, Oskar.

536
00:43:11,100 --> 00:43:13,200
You know it and I know it.

537
00:43:13,300 --> 00:43:15,600
Jews shoveling snow--

538
00:43:15,700 --> 00:43:20,400
It's got a, um,
ritual significance.

539
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:25,500
Come with me.
I am an essential worker.

540
00:43:25,600 --> 00:43:28,300
Essential worker?
[Laughing]
Yes.

541
00:43:28,300 --> 00:43:31,200
[Officer Laughing]

542
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:34,800
I work for Oskar Schindler.
Essential worker for Oskar Schindler.

543
00:43:34,900 --> 00:43:38,300
A one-armed Jew?
Twice as useless!
Yes, yes.

544
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:42,400
I lost a day
of production, Rolf.

545
00:43:42,500 --> 00:43:45,700
[Lowenstein]
I work for Oskar Schindler.

546
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:49,800
Danka, look at the snow.
Look at the snow.
Look at the snow!

547
00:43:49,900 --> 00:43:52,800
[Gunshot]

548
00:43:52,900 --> 00:43:57,700
I lost a worker.
I expect to be compensated.

549
00:43:57,800 --> 00:44:00,700
File a grievance
with the Economic Office.
It's your right.

550
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:03,500
Would it do
any good?
Of course not.

551
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:06,400
[Chuckles]

552
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:10,700
A big shot from the SS Budget
and Construction Office
came to lunch...

553
00:44:10,700 --> 00:44:14,400
and he told us that to believe
theJewish skilled worker
had a place...

554
00:44:14,400 --> 00:44:18,900
in Reich economics
was a treasonable idea.

555
00:44:22,300 --> 00:44:27,200
A one-armed machinist, Oskar?

556
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:29,700
He was
a metal press operator.

557
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:36,500
Quite skilled.

558
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:53,900
[Moaning]

559
00:45:02,300 --> 00:45:05,400
[Panting, Moaning]

560
00:45:05,500 --> 00:45:07,700
Herr Direktor?

561
00:45:07,700 --> 00:45:10,100
Shit.
I don't believe it.

562
00:45:10,100 --> 00:45:12,400
Stern, is that you?

563
00:45:12,500 --> 00:45:16,700
No, it's Poldek.
It's about Stern.

564
00:45:16,700 --> 00:45:20,600
[Soldier]
Leave your luggage
on the platform.

565
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:22,700
Clearly label it.

566
00:45:22,800 --> 00:45:27,000
Given name first,
then your surname.

567
00:45:27,100 --> 00:45:29,700
Do not bring
your baggage with you.

568
00:45:29,800 --> 00:45:32,700
It will follow you later.

569
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:36,000
Leave your luggage
on the platform.

570
00:45:36,100 --> 00:45:38,100
Clearly label it.

571
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:42,100
[Loudspeaker]
Lassen Sie Ihr Gepaeck
am Bahnsteig.

572
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:45,000
Stern?

573
00:45:47,100 --> 00:45:50,200
He's on the list.
He is?

574
00:45:50,300 --> 00:45:53,200
Well, let's find him.
I'm sorry.
You can't have him.

575
00:45:53,300 --> 00:45:56,200
He's on the list.
If he were an essential worker,
he would not be on the list.

576
00:45:56,300 --> 00:45:59,000
I'm talking to a clerk.
What is your name?

577
00:45:59,100 --> 00:46:02,200
Sir, the list is correct.
I didn't ask you about the list.

578
00:46:02,300 --> 00:46:06,400
I asked you your name.
Klaus Tauber.

579
00:46:06,500 --> 00:46:08,700
Tauber.

580
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:12,700
Hauptscharfuehrer,
this gentleman thinks
a mistake's been made.

581
00:46:12,700 --> 00:46:15,200
My plant manager is
somewhere on this train.

582
00:46:15,300 --> 00:46:17,400
If it leaves with him on it,
it'll disrupt production...

583
00:46:17,500 --> 00:46:19,700
and the Armaments Board
will want to know why.

584
00:46:19,800 --> 00:46:22,100
[Loudspeaker]
Achtung, dieser Zug
faehrt jetzt ab.

585
00:46:22,100 --> 00:46:26,300
Is he on the list?
Yes, sir. Itzhak Stern.

586
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:32,000
Well, the list is correct, sir.
There is nothing I can do.

587
00:46:32,100 --> 00:46:35,100
What is your name?
[Loudspeaker]
Close and secure all doors.

588
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:38,700
My name? My name is Kunder.
This train is now leaving.

589
00:46:38,700 --> 00:46:41,200
Kunder.
Hauptscharfuehrer Kunder.

590
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:43,200
K-U-N-D-E-R.
And what's yours?

591
00:46:43,200 --> 00:46:45,400
Schindler.
S-C-H-I-N-D-L-E-R.

592
00:46:45,500 --> 00:46:47,800
Gentlemen,
thank you very much.

593
00:46:47,900 --> 00:46:50,500
I think I can guarantee you
you'll both be in...

594
00:46:50,600 --> 00:46:54,300
Southern Russia before the
end of the month. Good day.

595
00:46:54,400 --> 00:46:57,400
[Conductor]
Zamykac dokladnie drzwi.
Dokladnie zamykac drzwi.

596
00:46:57,400 --> 00:46:59,500
Stern!

597
00:46:59,600 --> 00:47:01,500
Stern!
Stern!

598
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:03,500
Itzhak Stern!

599
00:47:03,600 --> 00:47:07,900
[Train Whistle Blowing]

600
00:47:09,900 --> 00:47:12,500
Stern!
Itzhak Stern!

601
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:15,400
[Kunder, Tauber]
Stern! Stern!
Itzhak Stern!

602
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:18,000
Stern!

603
00:47:18,100 --> 00:47:20,000
Sir?

604
00:47:21,400 --> 00:47:24,400
Stern!
Herr Direktor.

605
00:47:24,500 --> 00:47:27,300
[Coughing]
My apologies.

606
00:47:27,400 --> 00:47:30,300
Stop the train! He's here!
I apologize.

607
00:47:30,400 --> 00:47:35,400
- Stop the train!
- Stop the train! Stop it!

608
00:47:47,900 --> 00:47:51,700
Sign here. Initial there.
[Whistle Blowing]

609
00:47:51,800 --> 00:47:55,900
Makes no difference
to us, you understand.
This one, that one.

610
00:47:55,900 --> 00:47:58,500
[Train Whistle Blowing]
It's the inconvenience to the list.

611
00:47:58,600 --> 00:48:02,400
It's the paperwork.
I somehow left
my work card at home.

612
00:48:02,400 --> 00:48:06,200
I tried to explain them
it was a mistake, but--

613
00:48:06,300 --> 00:48:10,400
I'm sorry, it was stupid!
What if I got here
five minutes later?

614
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:13,200
Then where would I be?

615
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:55,300
Shechel.

616
00:49:55,400 --> 00:49:58,300
Sacrean,
sacrean end tzukeer.

617
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,900
Tzukeer end sacrean.

618
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:07,200
I woke up from a dream this morning.

619
00:50:07,300 --> 00:50:11,500
I was broke and sharing a room
with 12 people I didn't know,

620
00:50:11,600 --> 00:50:16,900
only to discover I was broke and sharing 
a room with 12 people I didn't know.

621
00:50:16,900 --> 00:50:17,900
[Chuckling]

622
00:50:17,900 --> 00:50:20,400
You laugh about it?
I have to laugh.

623
00:50:20,400 --> 00:50:23,400
You are living behind walls.

624
00:50:23,400 --> 00:50:28,200
The walls I can deal with.
It's the restrictions
to my life I'm tired of.

625
00:50:28,300 --> 00:50:31,400
Those walls keep them out.
That's all I care about.

626
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:34,200
I like it here.
There's a kind of,
I don't know,

627
00:50:34,300 --> 00:50:36,600
ancestral squalor to it all.

628
00:50:36,700 --> 00:50:38,900
You are a slave to these people.
No one envies us anymore.

629
00:50:39,000 --> 00:50:41,100
I'm smart.
Oh, yes, you're smart.

630
00:50:41,100 --> 00:50:43,400
You're a real genius.
You had your chance.

631
00:50:43,500 --> 00:50:48,200
Today, today I actually found time
to organize a thought.

632
00:50:48,300 --> 00:50:51,100
I can't remember
the last time I did that.

633
00:50:51,100 --> 00:50:53,100
When's the last time we did this?

634
00:50:53,100 --> 00:50:55,500
When's the last time
we stood around and talked?

635
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:58,900
No one ordered me
onto a truck today.

636
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:01,300
No one took my business away from me.

637
00:51:01,400 --> 00:51:03,400
You don't really have
a business to take.

638
00:51:03,500 --> 00:51:05,800
There's nowhere down from here.

639
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:08,100
This is it. This is the bottom.

640
00:51:08,200 --> 00:51:11,900
The ghetto is... liberty.

641
00:51:18,100 --> 00:51:21,400
This street divides the ghetto
just about in half.

642
00:51:21,500 --> 00:51:26,900
Right side, Ghetto A:
civil employees,

643
00:51:26,900 --> 00:51:29,900
industrial workers and so on.

644
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:34,900
Left side, Ghetto B: surplus labor,

645
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:37,400
the elderly and infirm mostly.

646
00:51:37,500 --> 00:51:40,500
Which is where you'll
want to start, huh?

647
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:42,500
Do you have any questions, sir?

648
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:46,200
Ja, why is the top down?
I'm fucking freezing.

649
00:51:48,400 --> 00:51:51,100
[Wilhelm Kunde]
We expect a labor force
of 25,000 to 30,000.

650
00:51:51,100 --> 00:51:54,200
Segregated, of course.
The men in the barracks near the quarry.

651
00:51:54,300 --> 00:51:55,600
The women on the other
side of the wire.

652
00:51:55,600 --> 00:51:58,200
[Goeth]
My place is where?
There, sir.

653
00:51:58,300 --> 00:52:01,700
There?
You call that a villa?
Yes, the villa.

654
00:52:01,800 --> 00:52:04,100
Their synagogue, can you see it?
That's not a villa.

655
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:07,500
We're planning to turn it
into the camp stables.
It's a house.

656
00:52:07,600 --> 00:52:11,400
[Goeth]
What's that over there?

657
00:52:11,500 --> 00:52:14,300
[Kunde]
Kindergarten.
Fifty-one.

658
00:52:14,300 --> 00:52:18,900
And we have a dentist, shoemaker,
practical physicians.

659
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:24,700
[Guard]
There they are, sir.

660
00:52:24,700 --> 00:52:27,800
[Goeth Sniffs]
Hmm.

661
00:52:27,900 --> 00:52:32,300
One of you is, uh,
a very lucky girl.

662
00:52:32,400 --> 00:52:36,200
There is an opening for a job,

663
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:40,200
away from all this...
backbreaking work,

664
00:52:40,300 --> 00:52:43,800
at my new villa.
[Sniffs]

665
00:52:43,900 --> 00:52:48,500
Uh, which of you has...

666
00:52:48,600 --> 00:52:51,400
domestic experience?

667
00:52:54,300 --> 00:52:58,500
Ja, on second thought,
I don't really want
someone else's maid.

668
00:52:58,600 --> 00:53:02,000
All those annoying habits
I have to undo.

669
00:53:06,900 --> 00:53:09,700
[Chuckles]
I don't want to give you my cold.

670
00:53:09,800 --> 00:53:12,000
Uh, what's your name?

671
00:53:12,100 --> 00:53:14,400
Helen Hirsch.
What?

672
00:53:14,500 --> 00:53:16,400
[Coughing]
Helen Hirsch.

673
00:53:16,500 --> 00:53:20,800
What? I can't hear.
Helen Hirsch.

674
00:53:36,600 --> 00:53:39,200
Ja.
[Woman]
Take it all down!

675
00:53:39,300 --> 00:53:41,700
[Officer Blows Whistle]
To work!

676
00:53:41,800 --> 00:53:46,200
[Woman Arguing]
Take it down!
It is not safe!

677
00:53:46,300 --> 00:53:49,000
She says the foundation was poured wrong.
She's got to take it down.

678
00:53:49,100 --> 00:53:52,200
I told her it's the barracks,
not the fucking Hotel Europa.

679
00:53:52,300 --> 00:53:56,600
Fucking Jew bitch engineer.
You fucking bitch!

680
00:53:56,600 --> 00:54:00,900
Herr Kommandant.
The entire foundation...

681
00:54:01,000 --> 00:54:03,700
has to be torn down
and repoured.

682
00:54:03,800 --> 00:54:07,200
If not, there will be
at least a subsidence...

683
00:54:07,300 --> 00:54:09,900
at the southern end
of the barracks.

684
00:54:10,000 --> 00:54:12,600
Subsidence, and then collapse.

685
00:54:12,600 --> 00:54:15,400
And you are an engineer?
Yes.

686
00:54:15,500 --> 00:54:17,900
My name is Diana Reiter.
I'm a graduate...

687
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:20,600
of Civil Engineering
from the University of Milan.

688
00:54:20,700 --> 00:54:24,500
Ah, an educated Jew,
like Karl Marx himself.

689
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:35,500
Unterscharfuehrer!
